# Poppy Playtime — Research for CG5 Template

> **Purpose**: Collected data to build `CG5_Poppy_Playtime.md` specialized template.
> **Focus**: Chapter 5 (Broken Things) + full character/location library across all chapters.

---

## 1. Lore Foundation

### Playtime Co.
- Founded by **Elliot Ludwig** in 1930 — toy manufacturer
- **Playcare**: On-site orphanage within factory
- Ludwig's daughter died → obsession with resurrection → experiments with "poppy gel"
- Created **Experiment 1006 (The Prototype)** and **Poppy doll** (Experiment 1007)
- Ludwig died in 1989 → company taken over by Leith Pierre & **Dr. Harley Sawyer**

### Bigger Bodies Initiative (BBI)
- Proposed by Dr. Harley Sawyer to save company from bankruptcy
- Secret program: transform orphans into giant living toys
- Process: sedate with red smoke → surgically transform into "Bigger Bodies"
- Goal: create immortal toy workforce

### The Hour of Joy (August 8, 1995)
- Living toys revolted and massacred nearly all factory staff
- Orchestrated by The Prototype
- Factory became abandoned, dangerous ruin — setting of the game

### Key Thematic Vocabulary
- "Paradise" = prison, "Fix you" = kill/transform, "New life" = reanimation
- "Home" = trap, "Better Place" = death/transformation
- "Bigger Bodies" = forced transformation of children into toys
- "Poppy gel" = substance that brings toys to life

---

## 2. Characters — Full Library

### 2.1 THE PROTOTYPE (Experiment 1006) — PRIMARY VILLAIN
- **Origin**: Human boy named Oliver (Elliot Ludwig's adopted son), first successful experiment
- **Appearance**: 
  - Massive entity, far larger than other experiments
  - Constructed from titanium, gears, wires, bones, and organic tissue
  - White porcelain-like doll face with wide unsettling smile, sharp elongated teeth
  - Long spindly arms with sharp clawed fingers
  - Eyes rotate like cameras
  - Jester motif: three-pointed hat with bells, red/yellow/blue outfit
  - Patchwork grotesque — grafts parts of defeated toys onto himself
- **Abilities**: Voice mimicry (posed as "Ollie"), extreme intelligence, assimilative power (absorbs defeated toys), violent
- **Motivation**: Believes transformation = immortality, sees himself as savior of experiments
- **Color**: White porcelain face, primary colors (R/Y/B), organic dark tones
- **Voice direction**: Manipulative, calm then explosive, god-complex, theatrical

### 2.2 HUGGY WUGGY (Experiment 1170) — Ch.1 & Ch.5
- **Appearance**: Tall slender humanoid, ~5.5m (18ft), covered in bright BLUE fur
- **Features**: Large yellow hands/feet with black Velcro strips, fused fingers/toes
- **Face**: Two big dilated black eyes, oversized red lips, thin blue bowtie
- **Teeth**: Dozens of jagged needle-like teeth behind lips, secondary jaws near throat (moray eel style)
- **Material**: Originally synthetic plush, Bigger Body = biological (muscle, cartilage, bone under fur)
- **Behavior**: Predatory stalker, stretches through vents, extremely fast
- **Role in Ch.5**: Returns as persistent threat, reunites with Kissy Missy, attacked/impaled by Prototype

### 2.3 KISSY MISSY (Experiment 1172) — Ally
- **Appearance**: Same structure as Huggy but PINK fur
- **Features**: Baby blue bow tie, yellow hands/feet, long fluttery eyelashes
- **Personality**: Kind, helpful — acts as ally to Player and Poppy
- **Role in Ch.5**: Helps Player and Poppy, attacked by Prototype alongside Huggy

### 2.4 POPPY (Experiment 1007) — Central Ally
- **Appearance**: Small porcelain doll (~40cm), chalk-white skin, 1950s vintage aesthetic
- **Features**: Curly RED hair in double pigtails with blue ribbons, large blue eyes (bloodshot over time), freckles, rosy cheeks, red lips
- **Attire**: Blue Victorian-style dress, white ruffled sleeves, white stockings, black Mary Jane shoes
- **Mechanism**: Pull-string on back
- **Material**: Porcelain (fragile, prone to cracking)
- **Origin**: Created from Elliot Ludwig's deceased daughter using organic parts
- **Ch.5**: Head cracked by Prototype, increasingly distressed appearance with bandages

### 2.5 LILY LOVEBRAIDS — Ch.5 Secondary Antagonist
- **Concept**: 90s fashion doll (Barbie/Bratz inspired), Playtime Co. dress-up toy
- **Key feature**: Controllable HAIR — braids move independently like extra limbs (scorpion tails/claws)
- **Hair biology**: Horse hair, grafted finger bones, biological materials
- **Physiology**: Arachnid-inspired (similar to Mommy Long Legs)
- **Face**: Doll-like but highly expressive, constricting pupils
- **Accessory**: Carries broken "Candy Cat" head — uses for ventriloquism (kind persona through doll, aggressive persona herself)
- **Outfits**: Pool party, circus/clown, princess, starry-night (dress-up doll identity)
- **Domain**: Traps Poppy and Kissy in her dollhouse-themed area ("Sweet Street")

### 2.6 GIBLET — Ch.5 New Ally (Deuteragonist)
- **Appearance**: Inside-out chihuahua/fox plush toy, orange-brown color
- **Features**: 
  - Left eye: magenta pupil, black iris shaped like four-petaled flower
  - Right eye: missing, black leather eyepatch
  - Metal bolt nose, square-shaped teeth
  - Matted brown fur patches on eyebrows, chin, limbs, ears, head top
  - "Inside-out" — exposed interior of plush body
- **Attire**: Frock coat, large Huggy Wuggy-themed button, patched mittens
- **Accessory**: Cane (doubles as taser, crafted from electrical components)
- **Stuffing**: Visibly poking out from mittens, left ear tip, head
- **Personality**: Resilient, positive but weary survivor

### 2.7 CHUM CHOMPKINS — Ch.5 Silent Ally
- **Appearance**: Large, plump, rotund creature with thick RED fur, yellow accents (stomach, hands, feet)
- **Signature**: First character with MOUTH ON STOMACH — holds/hides objects and player inside
- **Eyes**: Two offset eyes ("goofy" expression)
- **Texture**: Thick fluffy fur, small tufts on head, large chunky limbs
- **Behavior**: Mute, communicates via noises/body language/sign language
- **Role**: "Guy on the inside" for Giblet and Player, initially forced to work for Prototype

### 2.8 OUTIMALS — Ch.5 Minor Antagonists
- **Concept**: "Wrong side out" creatures, inspired by rejected 1990s toy line
- **Created by**: The Prototype as punishment/control mechanism
- **Types**:
  - **Rag Bags**: Critter-shaped head, inside-out plastic eyes, fur strips, hands circulate red blood-like liquid
  - **Gutter Plushes**: Larger, crocodile/dinosaur head (inverted teddy bears), asymmetrical eyes, blood-like liquid in hands
- **Behavior**: Territorial, aggressive, PHOTOPHOBIC (fear bright light)
- **Visual**: Inside-out appearance, inverted skin/fabric

### 2.9 MOMMY LONG LEGS (Experiment 1222) — Ch.2
- **Origin**: Human named Marie Payne, transformed via BBI
- **Appearance**: Tall slender humanoid, spider-like, primarily PINK
- **Face**: Large circular green eyes with white sclera, 3 eyelashes each, long black empty smile with pink lipstick
- **Hair**: Hot pink fringe, long noodle-like ponytail with light blue hair tie
- **Limbs**: Long thin ELASTIC arms/legs, can stretch to great lengths
- **Attire**: Hot pink gloves with light blue cuffs, matching shoes
- **Material**: "Elastic Plastic" — unique stretchy material
- **Inspired by**: Betty Spaghetty dolls (90s/2000s)

### 2.10 CATNAP (Experiment 1188) — Ch.3
- **Toy form**: Purple-furred anthropomorphic cat, triangular ears, black nose, very long tail
- **Bigger Body**: Large ominous feline monster, cold white eyes, fixed menacing smile
- **Ability**: Emits hallucinogenic toxic RED SMOKE — puts victims to sleep or kills
- **Personality**: Zealot worshipping The Prototype
- **Design origin**: "Cuddle Kitty" — zippered belly for nap-time

### 2.11 DOGDAY — Ch.3
- **Toy form**: Bright YELLOW anthropomorphic dog, optimistic/sunny leader of Smiling Critters
- **Bigger Body (mutilated)**: Bisected at waist, blood-stained torso, tan leather belt, oversized human-like hands, black stitches, empty black eye sockets, large toothless gaping mouth
- **Pendant**: Sun symbol

### 2.12 MISS DELIGHT — Ch.3
- **Design**: Ball-jointed teacher doll, segments connected at joints
- **Attire**: Torn crimson polka-dot skirt, light blue overalls (apple symbol), yellow office shirt, white collar, crimson tie, crimson shoes with blue embroidery
- **Face**: Once gentle with golden hair/crimson bow/rosy cheeks — now BROKEN, exposed flesh/teeth underneath
- **Behavior**: "Weeping Angel" mechanic — freezes when observed, sprints when unseen
- **Weapon**: "Barb" — makeshift morning star from sharpened pencils/pens with yellow ruler handle

### 2.13 YARNABY (Experiment 1166) — Ch.4 (DECEASED)
- **Design**: Cartoonish lion, 1970s wildlife conservation toy
- **Material**: Multicolored YARN mane and body
- **Face**: Amber-colored with black vertical seam
- **Eyes**: Large white cartoonish eyes, black dilated irises, small white pupils
- **Mouth**: Wide permanent grin, three asymmetric triangular fangs
- **Limbs**: Amber-colored, tan three-toed paws, no tail
- **Death**: Fell into molten metal in Ch.4

### 2.14 SMILING CRITTERS (Full Set) — Ch.3
All share: vibrant colors, chest zipper, wide toothless grin, black eyes with white pupils, unique pendant, scented pull-tail
- **Bubba Bubbaphant** (elephant, intelligence/brains, lemongrass scent)
- **Bobby BearHug** (bear, empathy, rose scent)
- **CraftyCorn** (unicorn, creativity/art, jasmine scent)
- **KickinChicken** (chicken, cool/fun)
- **Hoppy Hopscotch** (frog/rabbit, energetic)
- **PickyPiggy** (pig, food-loving)

### 2.15 DR. HARLEY SAWYER (The Doctor)
- **Status in Ch.5**: Consciousness uploaded to Playtime Co. servers as "Master Backup"
- **Appears as**: Digital AI eye on screen
- **Final line**: "Well now, this is a rather interesting turn of events."
- **Role going forward**: Uneasy alliance with Player against Prototype

